*Running Quiz*


~Beginning Page~
Beginning text: "Are you ready to hit the ground running?"
Button text: "Ready, set, go!"

~Question 1~
Question: "When speaking about running form, the leg that is currently behind 
your center of mass is referred to as what?"
A: "Lead Leg"
B: "Right Leg"
C: "Behind Leg"
D: "Trail Leg"
Correct Answer: D-"Trail Leg"

~Question 2~
Question: "In track & field, how many people are on a relay team?"
A: "5"
B: "10"
C: "4"
D: "The Amount Varies"
Correct Answer: C-"4"

~Question 3~
Question: "In a pre-run stretch routine, which type of stretching exercises are most often recommended?"
A: "Dynamic"
B: "Static"
C: "No Stretching"
D: "Stretching Types Do Not Vary"
Correct Answer: A-"Dynamic"

~Question 4~
Question: "When analyzing efficiency of running form, which measurement is the most important?"
A: "Stride Length"
B: "Force Applied To The Ground"
C: "Trunk(core-body) Positioning"
D: "All Are Equally As Important"
Correct Answer: D-"All Are Equally As Important"

~Question 5~
Question: "Which Type of Nutrient Is Most Crucial To Ingesting Post-Workout?"
A: "Calcium"
B: "Protein"
C: "Glucose"
D: "All Are Recommended For Post-workout Nutrition"
Correct Answer: D-"All are recommended for post-workout nutrition"

~Question 6~
Question: "What Is The Most Efficient Fuel Source During A Run?"
A: "Carbohydrates"
B: "Fats"
C: "Protein"
D: "Cake"
Correct Answer: B-"Fats"

~Question 7~
Question: "Which Nutrient Increases The Amount Of oxygen that individual red blood 
cells are able to carry?"
A: "Carbohydrates"
B: "Iron"
C: "Potassium"
D: "Protein"
Correct Answer: A-"Carbohydrates"

~Question 8~
Question: "Who currently(as of August, 2019) holds the official(and unofficial) world record 
for the marathon distance?"
A: "Wilson Kipsang"
B: "Mohammed Farah"
C: "Eliud Kipchoge"
D: "Galen Rupp"
Correct Answer: C-"Eliud Kipchoge"

~Question 9~
Question: "Living at which altitude is best for effective long-distance training?"
A: "low"
B: "Sea-level"
C: "High"
D: "Does not matter"
Correct Answer: C-"High"

~Question 10~
Question: "Who is the most dominant track & field sprinter of all time?"
A: "Michael Johnson"
B: "Carl Lewis"
C: "Usain Bolt"
D: "It's too subjective to call"
Correct Answer: C-"Usain Bolt"
